<div class="basictext">

	<div class="headtext">
	<a href="/recipe/kubideh">Kubideh</a>
	</div>

	<div class="basictext">
	Submitted by: Josh &lt;jmandel@snarked.com&gt;<br>
	Date: 2008-09-17<br>
	<br>
	</div>
<div class="recipetable" id="limitwidth">
<div class="ingredienttext">
<b>Ingredients:</b><br>large yellow onion, peeled and grated<br />
1 lb ground meat (lamb, beef, chicken thighs, whatever)<br />
1 clove garlic peeled and finely chopped<br />
1 egg, lightly beaten<br />
1/4 cup dry bread crumbs<br />
2 tsp salt<br />
1/2 tsp fresh ground pepper<br />
1/2 tsp ground turmeric<br />
1/4 tsp paprika<br />
1 pinch saffron threads<br />
1 tbsp butter, melted<br />
ground sumac & lemon wedges (optional garnish)</div><br><br>
<div class="instructiontext">
<b>Instructions</b><br>
Squeeze grated onion through cheesecloth to drain.  Mix onion, spices, and meat, and form into 8 logs.  Crumble  saffron into melted butter;  use this mixture to baste kebabs while grilling.

<br><br>

Recipe adapted from <a href="foodnerd">http://www.paisleysky.net/foodnerd/archives/000411.html</a>
</div>
